# Example email addresses

**Never commit real operator, household, or org notification addresses** in tracked files.

Use RFC 2606 placeholder domains only:

- `operator@example.com`, `resident@example.com`, `automation@example.com`, `alerts@example.com`
- `noreply@example.com` for SMTP from-address examples in tests

## Applies to

- `automation-rules.json.example` (`notification_emails`, `_notes`)
- `*.example` JSON/YAML bundles, committed test fixtures, and docs that ship example rule/mail config
- Hermetic tests that need a recipient string (prefer `ops@example.com` — already used in many rule tests)

## Do not use

- Personal or household inboxes (`@hcma.info`, `@kristenmather.com`, GitHub notification aliases tied to a real person, etc.)

## Exceptions

- **Gitignored operator data** (`automation-rules.json`, env files, systemd `EnvironmentFile=`) — real addresses belong only there.
- **Redaction tests** may mention a fake-looking address only to assert it is scrubbed from logs (not as a recommended pattern).

When editing an example file that still has legacy real addresses, replace them with `@example.com` placeholders in the same change.
